            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-02T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-02T12:00:00-05:00" n="332" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d332">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3–347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Butterworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-03T01:00:00+08:00">March 3, 1947—1 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received—3:13 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>424. Following from Taipei:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“March 2, 5 p.m. Light firing heard last night and throughout today, while
                        situation remains tense.</p>
                    <p>“In radio speech this afternoon Governor General agreed to people’s demands
                        as enunciated by local PPC<note n="10" xml:id="d332fn1">People’s Political
                            Council.</note> member acting as spokesman that all Formosans seized
                        during incident be released unconditionally <pb facs="0439" n="429" xml:id="pg_429"/> and that damages or medical treatment be given behalf
                        those killed and wounded. No reference in speech to other demands that
                        Monoply and Trading Bureau systems be abolished.</p>
                    <p>“All Government departments and services inoperative both Taipei-Keelung.
                        Island-wide disturbances reported.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Butterworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
